  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\nFollow up on the [sync of saved addresses PR]( https://github.com/status-im/status-go/pull/2865) to add incremental sync of saved address functionality.\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to sync saved addresses between paired devices.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nNotes\r\n\r\n- Full sync for saved addresses is done behind the scene on a manual sync\r\n- Incremental sync requires the following API calls changes\r\n  - Call `wakuext_upsertSavedAddress` instead of `wallet_addSavedAddress`\r\n  - Call `wakuext_deleteSavedAddress` instead of `wallet_deleteSavedAddress`\r\n- Dynamic reloading of changes after sync requires processing `MessengerResponse` and checking for `savedAddresses` json array entries to be reloaded for all the wallet changes.\r\n- Remove wallet saved addresses API endpoints that were replaced with messenger calls\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nDevices A and B are paired\r\n- [ ] Adding or making changes to a new address on device A will reflect in device B when online\r\n- [ ] On the device B, when receiving a change from device A should be reflected in the saved address list (Favourites view)",
